New signings Diego Costa and Cesc Fabregas looked at home straight away as they took part in a Chelsea training session led by manager Jose Mourinho in Austria.

The duo, signed from Atletico Madrid and Barcelona this summer respectively, looked refreshed and in high spirits - despite their involvement in Spain's disastrous World Cup.

Costa flew in overnight from Lisbon and joined up with the Chelsea squad early on Monday morning before boarding a plane with the rest of the squad.

